==English==

===Proper Noun===
'''Hamm'''
# an [[English]] [[topographic]] [[surname]] for someone who lived in an area of flat land near a river; or a [[habitational]] name from several places with the same name in southern [[England]]
# a [[German]] topographic or habitational surname with a similar etymology

===Verb===
'''to Hamm'''
# to deceive, with the willful intent of mocking or humiliating another person. Used to describe the deception of gullible people. ie. "You've been hammed"